<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><ComponentSpec xmlns:clariah="http://www.clariah.eu/" xmlns:cue="http://www.clarin.eu/cmd/cues/1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" isProfile="true" CMDVersion="1.2" CMDOriginalVersion="1.2" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="https://infra.clarin.eu/CMDI/1.x/xsd/cmd-component.xsd">
	<Header>
		<ID>clarin.eu:cr1:p_1758888743558</ID>
		<Name>Person</Name>
		<Description>This is a test profile for registering Person-related data according to the PiCo and CIDOC-CRM data models. It is inspired by: https://docs.swissartresearch.net/et/persons/. It is not strictly compliant with those models, but it aims to operationalize both approaches for data entry.
			From PiCo it implements the concept of "Observation". It follows PiCo's main principle that "A person observation represents how a person is recorded on a Source. Therefore, it must always be related to a source. Person observations closely reflect data as it appears in the source, that is, with the age, occupation, and spelling of the person's name recorded as in the record."
			However, this Profile can also be used for "Reconstructions" or Person-related data in general:
			- If the aim is to record observations from ONE source: enter the source's basic metadata, and use the profile as it is, where there are components and elements to register "labels" as observed, plus confidence for those observations. Make sure that the cardinality of the Source component is 1-1 in your local implementation.
			- If the aim is to record person-related data combined from different sources, without the need to keep provenance for every single element, only for the aggregated data in the record, use "Source" to enter all the sources used to extract the data. Also, the elements/components that keep provenance at each level can be removed in the local implementation. Make sure that the cardinality of the Source component is 1-unbounded in your local implementation.</Description>
		<Status>development</Status>
	</Header>
